    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Designates the period of the rule of King Jayavarman I (657-681CE) over the pre-Angkor kingdom of Chen-la. Artistic production in this period emulates Hindu models and is motivated by the Indian epics of Mahbhrata and Rmyaa.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
